org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulator.mutable

Interface VariantData<E,T extends VariantData<E,T,I>,I extends ImmutableVariantData<E,I,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element value being represented
    T - The type of mutable variant data for mutability
    I - The type of immutable variant data being extended
    All Superinterfaces:
    DataManipulator<T,I>, DataSerializable, ValueContainer<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ArtData, AxisData, BigMushroomData, BrickData, CareerData, CoalData, ComparatorData, CookedFishData, DirtData, DisguisedBlockData, DominantHandData, DoublePlantData, DyeableData, FishData, GameModeData, GoldenAppleData, HingeData, LogAxisData, OcelotData, ParrotData, PickupRuleData, PistonData, PlantData, PortionData, PrismarineData, QuartzData, RabbitData, RailDirectionData, RotationalData, SandData, SandstoneData, ShrubData, SkullData, SlabData, SpawnableData, StairShapeData, StoneData, TreeData, WallData
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSingleCatalogData

    public interface VariantData<E,T extends VariantData<E,T,I>,I extends ImmutableVariantData<E,I,T>>
extends DataManipulator<T,I>
    Represents a type of DataManipulator handling a specific type of element, usually CatalogTypes. The advantage is that type() will always return the same type as a Value.
